§
Section 1

¶	PAR:par_default_scope

The ID (‘PAR:par_default_scope’) of this paragraph has default
(global) scope. It may be referred to from anywhere in the document.


¶	PAR:par:GBL

The ID (‘PAR:par:GBL’) of this paragraph has explicitly global scope.



§
Section 2

¶	PAR:par:SEC

The ID (‘PAR:par:SEC’) of this paragraph has section scope. We may
still refer to [PAR:par:GBL], by using ‘\[PAR:par:GBL]’.

¶

Some cross-references:

-	‘\[PAR:par_default_scope]’: [PAR:par_default_scope]

-	‘\[PAR:par:GBL]’:           [PAR:par:GBL]

-	‘\[PAR:par:SEC]’:           [PAR:par:SEC]


§
Section 3

¶	PAR:par:SEC

The ID (‘PAR:par:SEC’) of this paragraph has section scope. Since it
has section scope there is no problem that it has the same ID as a
paragraph in another section.

¶

Some cross-references:

-	‘\[PAR:par_default_scope]’: [PAR:par_default_scope]

-	‘\[PAR:par:GBL]’:           [PAR:par:GBL]

-	‘\[PAR:par:SEC]’:           [PAR:par:SEC]
